HEADWORD: magnetic disk
<hw>magnetic disk</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A ditical memory device consisting of a flat disk covered with a
magnetic coating on which information is stored; a <stype>hard
disk</stype>, <stype>floppy disk</stype>, and <stype>diskette</stype>
are typically magnetic disks.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> disk, disc.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

